description:
If the current quote is deleted, the app shows nothing until midnight rotation.

**Location:** `src/services/dailyQuote.ts` lines 29-33

**Problem:**
```typescript
if (currentId) {
  return getQuoteById(currentId);  // Returns null if quote was deleted
}
return null;  // App shows empty state
```

**Scenario:**
1. Quote #5 is set as current quote
2. User deletes quote #5 from the list
3. User returns to home screen
4. `rotateQuoteIfNeeded` returns null because quote #5 doesn't exist
5. Home screen shows empty/default state until midnight

**Fix:** If `getQuoteById(currentId)` returns null but currentId was set, clear the stale ID and pick a new quote:

```typescript
if (currentId) {
  const quote = await getQuoteById(currentId);
  if (quote) return quote;
  // Quote was deleted, clear stale reference and rotate
  await setCurrentQuoteId(null);
}
return rotateQuote();
```

**Also:** When deleting a quote (`app/quotes/index.tsx`), check if it's the current quote and trigger rotation.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Deleting current quote immediately shows a new quote
- [ ] No stale quote IDs left in settings
- [ ] Background task doesn't fail due to deleted quote

invalidateCache can crash the app if file operations fail.

**Location:** `src/services/wallpaperCache.ts` lines 56-76

**Problem:**
```typescript
export function invalidateCache(quoteId?: number): void {
  const dir = getWallpaperDir();
  if (!dir.exists) return;

  const contents = dir.list();  // Can throw
  // ...
  for (const file of files) {
    file.delete();  // Can throw
  }
}
```

No try-catch around file operations. If any operation fails (permissions, disk full, etc.), the error propagates to UI code in settings.tsx and quotes screens, potentially crashing the app.

**Fix:**
```typescript
export function invalidateCache(quoteId?: number): void {
  try {
    const dir = getWallpaperDir();
    if (!dir.exists) return;
    // ... rest of logic
  } catch (error) {
    logger.error('Error invalidating cache:', error);
    // Fail silently - cache will be stale but app won't crash
  }
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] File operation errors are caught and logged
- [ ] App doesn't crash when cache invalidation fails
- [ ] User can still delete quotes even if cache cleanup fails

Move StyleSheet.create calls from inside components to module scope.

**Problem:** StyleSheet.create inside component functions recreates style objects on every render, causing unnecessary allocations.

**Files to fix (6 total):**
- `app/index.tsx` (line ~123)
- `app/settings.tsx` (line ~87)
- `app/quotes/index.tsx` (line ~70)
- `app/quotes/[id].tsx` (line ~72)
- `app/quotes/import.tsx` (line ~178)
- `app/categories.tsx` (line ~63)

**Files already correct:** WallpaperPreview.tsx, WallpaperGenerator.tsx ✓

**Pattern to follow:**
```typescript
// BEFORE (inside component)
export default function Screen() {
  const { colors } = useTheme();
  const styles = StyleSheet.create({ container: { backgroundColor: colors.bg } });
  ...
}

// AFTER (at module scope, dynamic colors inline)
export default function Screen() {
  const { colors } = useTheme();
  return <View style={[styles.container, { backgroundColor: colors.bg }]} />;
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: { flex: 1 },
});
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] All 6 files have StyleSheet.create at module scope
- [ ] Theme-dependent colors applied via inline styles or style arrays
- [ ] No visual regressions
